<div class="col-md-6"> 

We are presenting here the example of an escrow system, subdivided into a step-by-step process:<br>
<ol>
	<li> Buyer <a href="http://www.commonaccord.org/index.php?action=source&file=Doc/core/id/roberta_robinson">Roberta Robinson</a> wants to purchase a product from Seller <a href="http://www.commonaccord.org/index.php?action=source&file=Doc/core/id/gerrys_grapes_llc"> Gerry's Grapes</a></li>
	<li>Parties agree on the <a href="http://www.commonaccord.org/index.php?action=source&file=Doc/core/form/agt/escrow/Form">Template Agreement</a> and <a href="http://www.commonaccord.org/index.php?action=source&file=Doc/core/form/agt/escrow/JAMS_Arbitration_Chicago">Arbitration Rules</a> for the transaction</li>
	<li> Paries introduce their names as Parameters into the Template agreement and get a <a href="http://www.commonaccord.org/index.php?action=source&file=Doc/doc/escrow/Demo_Escrow_Step_1_Parties">new version</a> of the Agreement (step 1)</li>
	<li> Parties specify the details of the <a href="http://www.commonaccord.org/index.php?action=source&file=Doc/doc/escrow/Demo_Escrow_Step_2_Order">Order</a> into the contract, and generate a <a href="http://www.commonaccord.org/index.php?action=source&file=Doc/doc/escrow/Demo_Escrow_Step_2_Order">second version</a> of the Agreement (step 2)</li>
	<li> Parties sign the contract and get a <a href="http://www.commonaccord.org/index.php?action=source&file=Doc/doc/escrow/Demo_Escrow_Step_3_Signature">final version</a> of the Agreement (step 3)</li>
</ol>
 </div>
